#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.217"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.217:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.217:0.2"
msgid "21. Karajakāyavagga"
msgstr "21. The Body Born of Deeds"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.217:0.3"
msgid "217. Paṭhamasañcetanikasutta"
msgstr "217. Intentional (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.292"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: appaṭisaṃveditvā → appaṭisaṃviditvā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.217:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ "
"appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and "
"accumulated are eliminated without being experienced."

msgctxt "an10.217:1.2"
msgid "Tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some "
"subsequent period."

msgctxt "an10.217:1.3"
msgid ""
"Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ "
"appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional "
"deeds that have been performed and accumulated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā → akusalaṃ sañcetanikaṃ dukkhudrayaṃ dukkhavipākaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an10.217:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā "
"dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti;"
msgstr ""
"Now, there are three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action that "
"have unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result."

msgctxt "an10.217:2.2"
msgid ""
"catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā "
"dukkhavipākā hoti;"
msgstr ""
"There are four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action that have "
"unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result."

msgctxt "an10.217:2.3"
msgid ""
"tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā "
"dukkhavipākā hoti."
msgstr ""
"There are three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action that have "
"unskillful intention, with suffering as their outcome and result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā "
"dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And what are the three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action?"

msgctxt "an10.217:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātī hoti, luddo lohitapāṇi hatapahate "
"niviṭṭho adayāpanno sabbapāṇabhūtesu. (1)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a certain person kills living creatures. They’re violent, bloody-"
"handed, a hardened killer, merciless to living beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:4.1"
msgid ""
"Adinnādāyī hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ gāmagataṃ vā araññagataṃ "
"vā, taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"They steal. With the intention to commit theft, they take the wealth or "
"belongings of others from village or wilderness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:5.1"
msgid ""
"Kāmesumicchācārī hoti, yā tā māturakkhitā … pe … antamaso "
"mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu cārittaṃ āpajjitā hoti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"They commit sexual misconduct. They have sex with women who have their "
"mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or clan "
"as guardian. They have sex with a woman who is protected on principle, or "
"who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or even one who "
"has been garlanded as a token of betrothal."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:6.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā "
"dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti."
msgstr "These are the three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.293"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:7.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti "
"akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti?"
msgstr "And what are the four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action?"

msgctxt "an10.217:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco musāvādī hoti. Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā "
"ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto "
"sakkhipuṭṭho "
msgstr ""
"It’s when a certain person lies. They’re summoned to a council, an assembly, "
"a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: "

msgctxt "an10.217:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, "
"jānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘na "
"passāmī’ti, iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā sampajānamusā "
"bhāsitā hoti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I know.’ "
"Knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I see.’ And seeing, "
"they say ‘I don’t see.’ So they deliberately lie for the sake of themselves "
"or another, or for some trivial worldly reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:8.1"
msgid ""
"Pisuṇavāco hoti, ito sutvā amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā "
"imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. Iti samaggānaṃ vā bhettā bhinnānaṃ vā "
"anuppadātā vaggārāmo vaggarato vagganandī, vaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
"(5)"
msgstr ""
"They speak divisively. They repeat in one place what they heard in another "
"so as to divide people against each other. And so they divide those who are "
"harmonious, supporting division, delighting in division, loving division, "
"speaking words that promote division."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:9.1"
msgid ""
"Pharusavāco hoti, yā sā vācā aṇḍakā kakkasā parakaṭukā parābhisajjanī "
"kodhasāmantā. Asamādhisaṃvattanikā, tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"They speak harshly. They use the kinds of words that are cruel, nasty, "
"hurtful, offensive, bordering on anger, not leading to immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:10.1"
msgid ""
"Samphappalāpī hoti, akālavādī abhūtavādī anatthavādī adhammavādī "
"avinayavādī, anidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti akālena anapadesaṃ "
"apariyantavatiṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ. (7)"
msgstr ""
"They indulge in talking nonsense. Their speech is untimely, and is neither "
"factual nor beneficial. It has nothing to do with the teaching or the "
"training. Their words have no value, and are untimely, unreasonable, "
"rambling, and pointless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:11.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasandosabyāpatti "
"akusalasañcetanikā dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti."
msgstr "These are the four kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:12.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā "
"dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And what are the three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action?"

msgctxt "an10.217:12.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ, "
"taṃ abhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata, yaṃ parassa taṃ mama assā’ti. (8)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone is covetous. They covet the wealth and belongings of "
"others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:13.1"
msgid ""
"Byāpannacitto hoti, paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā bajjhantu "
"vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā ahesun’ti. (9)"
msgstr ""
"They have ill will and hateful intentions: ‘May these sentient beings be "
"killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or annihilated!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.294"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:14.1"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhiko hoti, viparītadassano:"
msgstr "They have wrong view. Their perspective is distorted:"

msgctxt "an10.217:14.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi dinnaṃ … pe … ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. (10)"
msgstr ""
"‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or "
"result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There’s no obligation to "
"mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no "
"ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the "
"afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:15.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasandosabyāpatti akusalasañcetanikā "
"dukkhudrayā dukkhavipākā hoti."
msgstr "These are the three kinds of corruption and failure of mental action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
#. VAR: Tividhakāyakammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu → … sañcetanikahetu (mr)
msgctxt "an10.217:16.1"
msgid ""
"Tividhakāyakammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, "
"sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ "
"upapajjanti; catubbidhavacīkammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, "
"bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapajjanti; tividhamanokammantasandosabyāpatti "
"akusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell because of these three "
"kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action, these four kinds of "
"corruption and failure of verbal action, or these three kinds of corruption "
"and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with suffering "
"as their outcome and result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:17.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, apaṇṇako maṇi uddhaṅkhitto yena yeneva patiṭṭhāti "
"suppatiṭṭhitaṃyeva patiṭṭhāti;"
msgstr "It’s like throwing loaded dice: they always fall the right side up."

msgctxt "an10.217:17.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, "
"tividhakāyakammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; "
"catubbidhavacīkammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjanti; "
"tividhamanokammantasandosabyāpattiakusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa "
"bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantīti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are "
"reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell because of "
"these three kinds of corruption and failure of bodily action, these four "
"kinds of corruption and failure of verbal action, or these three kinds of "
"corruption and failure of mental action that have unskillful intention, with "
"suffering as their outcome and result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:18.1"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ "
"appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi, "
msgstr ""
"I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated "
"are eliminated without being experienced. "

msgctxt "an10.217:18.2"
msgid "tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some "
"subsequent period."

msgctxt "an10.217:18.3"
msgid ""
"Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ "
"appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional "
"deeds that have been performed and accumulated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.295"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:19.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā "
"sukhavipākā hoti;"
msgstr ""
"Now, there are three kinds of successful bodily action that have skillful "
"intention, with happiness as their outcome and result."

msgctxt "an10.217:19.2"
msgid ""
"catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā "
"hoti;"
msgstr ""
"There are four kinds of successful verbal action that have skillful "
"intention, with happiness as their outcome and result."

msgctxt "an10.217:19.3"
msgid ""
"tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti."
msgstr ""
"There are three kinds of successful mental action that have skillful "
"intention, with happiness as their outcome and result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:20.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā "
"sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti?"
msgstr "And what are the three kinds of successful bodily action?"

msgctxt "an10.217:20.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti nihitadaṇḍo nihitasattho "
"lajjī dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharati … pe …. (1)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a certain person gives up killing living creatures. They renounce "
"the rod and the sword. They’re scrupulous and kind, living full of "
"compassion for all living beings."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:21.1"
msgid ""
"Adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ gāmagataṃ vā "
"araññagataṃ vā, na taṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātā hoti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"They don’t steal. They don’t, with the intention to commit theft, take the "
"wealth or belongings of others from village or wilderness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:22.1"
msgid ""
"Kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti. Yā tā "
"māturakkhitā … pe … antamaso mālāguḷaparikkhittāpi, tathārūpāsu na cārittaṃ "
"āpajjitā hoti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"They give up sexual misconduct. They don’t have sex with women who have "
"their mother, father, both mother and father, brother, sister, relatives, or "
"clan as guardian. They don’t have sex with a woman who is protected on "
"principle, or who has a husband, or whose violation is punishable by law, or "
"even one who has been garlanded as a token of betrothal."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:23.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā kāyakammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā "
"sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti."
msgstr "These are the three kinds of successful bodily action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:24.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā "
"sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti?"
msgstr "And what are the four kinds of successful verbal action?"

msgctxt "an10.217:24.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti. "
"Sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato vā pūgamajjhagato vā "
"rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho ‘ehambho purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ "
"vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, "
"apassaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, iti attahetu vā "
"parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā na sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a certain person gives up lying. They’re summoned to a council, an "
"assembly, a family meeting, a guild, or to the royal court, and asked to "
"bear witness: ‘Please, mister, say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I "
"don’t know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ "
"And seeing, they say ‘I see.’ They don’t deliberately lie for the sake of "
"themselves or another, or for some trivial worldly reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.296"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:25.1"
msgid ""
"Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti—na ito sutvā amutra "
"akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ bhedāya. "
"Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato "
"samagganandiṃ, samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"They give up divisive speech. They don’t repeat in one place what they heard "
"in another so as to divide people against each other. Instead, they "
"reconcile those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting in harmony, "
"loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:26.1"
msgid ""
"Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti. Yā sā vācā nelā "
"kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā, "
"tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"They give up harsh speech. They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to "
"the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the "
"people."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:27.1"
msgid ""
"Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti kālavādī bhūtavādī "
"atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti kālena "
"sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ. (7)"
msgstr ""
"They give up talking nonsense. Their words are timely, true, and meaningful, "
"in line with the teaching and training. They say things at the right time "
"which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:28.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catubbidhā vacīkammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā "
"sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti."
msgstr "These are the four kinds of successful verbal action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:29.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā "
"sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti?"
msgstr "And what are the three kinds of successful mental action?"

msgctxt "an10.217:29.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti. Yaṃ taṃ parassa "
"paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ anabhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata, yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’"
"ti. (8)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone is content. They don’t covet the wealth and belongings of "
"others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:30.1"
msgid ""
"Abyāpannacitto hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā hontu abyāpajjā "
"anīghā, sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti. (9)"
msgstr ""
"They have a kind heart and loving intentions: ‘May these sentient beings "
"live free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:31.1"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhiko hoti aviparītadassano:"
msgstr "They have right view, an undistorted perspective:"

msgctxt "an10.217:31.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ … pe … ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti. (10)"
msgstr ""
"‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and "
"results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There is obligation to "
"mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are "
"ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe "
"the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:32.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhā manokammantasampatti kusalasañcetanikā "
"sukhudrayā sukhavipākā hoti."
msgstr "These are the three kinds of successful mental action."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:33.1"
msgid ""
"Tividhakāyakammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; "
"catubbidhavacīkammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; "
"tividhamanokammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā, bhikkhave, sattā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are reborn in a good "
"place, in heaven because of these three kinds of successful bodily action, "
"these four kinds of successful verbal action, or these three kinds of "
"successful mental action that have skillful intention, with happiness as "
"their outcome and result."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.297"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "an10.217:34.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, apaṇṇako maṇi uddhaṅkhitto yena yeneva patiṭṭhāti "
"suppatiṭṭhitaṃyeva patiṭṭhāti;"
msgstr "It’s like throwing loaded dice: they always fall the right side up."

msgctxt "an10.217:34.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, tividhakāyakammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā "
"sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; "
"catubbidhavacīkammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti; "
"tividhamanokammantasampattikusalasañcetanikāhetu vā sattā kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when their body breaks up, after death, sentient beings are "
"reborn in a good place, in heaven because of these three kinds of successful "
"bodily action, these four kinds of successful verbal action, or these three "
"kinds of successful mental action that have skillful intention, with "
"happiness as their outcome and result."

msgctxt "an10.217:34.3"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ "
"appaṭisaṃveditvā byantībhāvaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"I don’t say that intentional deeds that have been performed and accumulated "
"are eliminated without being experienced."

msgctxt "an10.217:34.4"
msgid "Tañca kho diṭṭheva dhamme upapajje vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And that may be in the present life, or in the next life, or in some "
"subsequent period."

msgctxt "an10.217:34.5"
msgid ""
"Na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sañcetanikānaṃ kammānaṃ katānaṃ upacitānaṃ "
"appaṭisaṃveditvā dukkhassantakiriyaṃ vadāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And I don’t say that suffering is ended without experiencing intentional "
"deeds that have been performed and accumulated.”"

#. VAR: Sattamaṃ → aṭṭhakathāyaṃ pana aṭṭhamasuttampi ettheva pariyāpannaṃ viya saṃvaṇṇanā
msgctxt "an10.217:34.6"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
